### What is the Bin Packing Problem?
The Bin Packing Problem is a well-known problem in computer science where you have a set of items of various sizes and a set of bins of fixed capacity. The goal is to pack the items into the bins using as few bins as possible. In this case, the heuristic will assign the next item to the bin with the highest priority, which is determined by the function `priority(item, bins)`.
</think>

